/**
 * /service-testing/multifamily-v3 — V3 of the multifamily service
 * page.
 *
 * Same exact content as v2 (data duplicated below — single source
 * of truth for THIS page so it stays self-contained), rendered
 * through the existing ServicePageV2 template, then visually
 * unified by a global stylesheet override that:
 *
 *   - Replaces the V2 page's light cool gradient with a single
 *     continuous dark-teal canvas (#142631 → #1A2F3A → #142631).
 *   - Strips solid background colors + box-shadow/clip-path
 *     bg-extension tricks from EVERY dark section (`pain`,
 *     `hardware`, `software`, `proof`, `faq`) so they all just
 *     show the page canvas — meaning every dark-section boundary
 *     is now invisible (the "page is dark, the section is
 *     transparent" trick).
 *   - Re-renders light sections (`narrative`, `scope`, `fin`,
 *     `finalCta`) as **feathered light bands** that fade in
 *     from transparent at the top, hold solid in the middle,
 *     and fade back to transparent at the bottom. Where the
 *     band's edge fades to transparent, the dark canvas shows
 *     through cleanly — no hard boundary line, just a gradient
 *     dissolve from light into dark.
 *   - Adds two large atmospheric green orbs that drift behind
 *     the content for cohesive ambient depth across all sections.
 *
 * The overrides are applied via `<style is:global>` keyed on a
 * runtime-set `html.svc-v3-active` flag — the inline script at
 * the top of the page sets that class before any V2 content
 * paints, so the V3 visual lands without flash. ServicePageV2
 * itself is untouched: same render block, same data shape, same
 * scoped styles. V3 just bolts a fresh visual skin on top.
 */
